@bondj Thanks for the update. 

One thing to note is that any invalid url will no longer be a part of the bootstrap, even if it is resolvable later because most usage is something like this:

``` scala
List<InetSocketAddress> addresses = ClientUtils.parseAndValidateAddresses(config.getList(ConsumerConfig.BOOTSTRAP_SERVERS_CONFIG));
this.metadata.update(Cluster.bootstrap(addresses), 0);
```

I would like some others to confirm thats acceptable. @ewencp @ijuma ?

The name of the method `parseAndValidateAddresses` doesn't make it totally clear that it could filter out and return a subset of addresses, though its purpose is clearly for bootstrap use given the logging inside the method and its current usage in the project. I think some simple javadoc on the behavior of the method would be useful. 

Otherwise LGTM.

This patch is definitely an improvement, and LGTM.

Longer term we likely want to define zookeeper compatibility a bit more concretely. 

Currently `ZkUtils.registerBrokerInZk` still sets host, port, and jmx_port for V2 json even though V2 only uses endpoints. That makes sense for compatibility if the V1 option would be tried when any other version is seen. I suspect when we add a V3 or V4 we would also maintain writing the older fields for V1 & V2 in `ZkUtils.registerBrokerInZk`. It could make sense to have the parsing logic in `Broker.createBroker` (or anything reading Json from Zookeeper) try all known versions in descending order from the version received from ZK. but perhaps that logic is too loose. 

A generic function to capture whatever rule is defined such as `parseVersionedJson` could take functions for each versions and return the successful result or fail. Rough pseudo code for examples sake:

``` scala
def parseVersionedJson[T](json: String, versionedParsers: Map[Int, String => T]): T = {
  Json.parseFull(json) match {
    case Some(m) =>
      val fields = m.asInstanceOf[Map[String, Any]]
      val version = fields("version").asInstanceOf[Int]
      if(versionedParsers.contains(version)) {
        versionedParsers(version)(json)
      } else {
        val parsers = versionedParsers.toSeq.sortBy(_._1)
        // loop over parsers trying to parse, error if all fail
        ...
      }
    case None =>
      throw new RuntimeException(s"Could not parse json string: $json")
  }
}
```
